      "side": 1,
      "message": "Use an error tag for this, or a constant error, e.g.\n\n  var OutOfOrderTag \u003d errors.BoolTag{\n    Key: errors.NewTagKey(\"Trying to apply N data after N+1 has been processed.\")\n  }\n\n  return errors.Reason(\"something bad: %s\", data).Tag(OutOfOrderTag).Err()\n\n  if OutOfOrderTag.In(err) {\n    // do stuff\n  }\n\nOR\n\n  var OutOfOrderErr \u003d errors.New(\"stuff is out of order, yo\")\n\n  return errors.Annotate(OutOfOrderErr, \"something bad: %s\", data).Err()\n\n  if errors.Unwrap(err) \u003d\u003d OutOfOrderErr {\n    // do stuff\n  }\n\nI would prefer the first over the second.",
